  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing the Visuals**\n\nOkay, I\'m now focusing on the visual identity of the Research Digest application. I\'m taking the user requirements into consideration: two AI agents in sequence, persistence in Firestore, a simple history view, and a single input field for the topic with a \'Generate Digest\' button. The design needs to be clean, intuitive, and reflect the underlying AI-powered functionality.\n\n\n**Defining the Glitch Aesthetics**\n\nI\'m now diving deep into defining the retro-futuristic, glitch art aesthetic. The core visual elements are coming into focus: a dark, CRT-like background, neon cyan and magenta accents for highlights and borders, and a pixelated monospace font. I\'ve chosen Share Tech Mono for the UI text, to be rendered with jarring color contrasts to emphasize the intended machine-like tone.\n\n\n**Implementing the Aesthetic**\n\nI\'m now getting into the coding specifics, and this is where it gets really fun! I\'m planning out the CSS modifications for the glitch aesthetic. I\'ll need to define custom fonts, scanlines, glitch effects, and neon styles in `src/index.css`, but first, I\'ll review the current file, which is just `@import \"tailwindcss\";` right now. I\'ve confirmed we\'re using Tailwind CSS v4, so the theme configuration will be direct. The magenta buttons with black text that turn cyan on hover are definitely next on my list.\n\n\\n\\n\n\nI\'m making progress implementing the machine-like messaging. I\'m excited about the cryptic tone. I\'m going to create strings like: \"INITIALIZING SEQUENTIAL NEURAL PIPELINE...\", and \"AGENT_1: RESEARCHER DEPLOYED. RETRIEVING FACTUAL NODES VIA WEB GROUNDING...\". I\'m thinking of \"STATUS: COMPLETED. COLD STORAGE COMMITTED\" as the final message. Custom classes or keyframe animations are going to be used in `/src/index.css` for scanlines, glitch text, screen flicker, and static noise.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 13
      nanos: 546379989
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
