  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Confirming Initial Setup**\n\nI\'m pleased to report that the development server is up and running, exactly as configured! It seems the restart went smoothly, and all indications point to proper port and configuration settings. Now, I\'m shifting focus to reviewing the user\'s initial requirements to make sure nothing was missed.\n\n\n**Analyzing Agent Architectures**\n\nI\'ve successfully implemented two agents. Agent 1 efficiently gathers and structures factual data from web searches on a given topic, producing JSON output. Agent 2 then takes this output and synthesizes it into a concise, readable digest report. I am confident both work reliably and the implementation of `/src/gemini.ts` for both agents is working to expectations. I am starting to consider the next stages of the process.\n\n**Storing Digests in Firestore**\n\nI\'ve now implemented persistent storage for the generated digests. Each report, along with its associated topic and timestamp, is saved to Firestore. A history view is accessible that lists past digests. It pulls the data from Firestore, newest first, for easy re-access. The solution in `/src/firebase.ts` should function as expected.\n\n\n**Designing the UI**\n\nI\'ve completed the UI implementation. The user interface has a field for topic input and a \"Generate Digest\" button, with results displayed. There\'s also a sidebar history list. The responsive columns, loading spinners, and interactive elements are functioning. I am also happy that the agents are separated into two functions, and the visual style is complete!\n\n\n**Finalizing Report Generation**\n\nI\'m ready to produce the final system diagnostic report. I\'ve ensured a cryptic, machine-like tone with helpful information, adhering to all style specifications. The report will feature a proportional scale and form, with bullet points for easy scanning of functional modules, like instructed. There are no internal details like Step IDs or file paths included, just high-level functional outcomes. The final compilation process did complete successfully and perfectly compliant with the instructions.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "### COGNITIVE PIPELINE STABILIZED // DIRECTIVE EXECUTED\n\n```\n[SYSTEM LOG] BOOTSTRAP SEQUENCE COMPLETED.\n[SYSTEM LOG] PIPELINE INTERFACE RE-INITIALIZED.\n[SYSTEM LOG] ALL ARTIFACTS COMMITTED AND VERIFIED.\n```\n\nI have completed the multi-agent **Research Digest** application, structured around a sequential neural pipeline. The visual envelope has been crafted around a **Glitch Art / Retro-Futurist UI** style featuring raw monospace typography, glowing neon line margins, and screen-tearing overlays.\n\n---\n\n### // SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE SUMMARY\n\n#### 1. Dual-Agent Sequential Pipeline\n- **Agent 1: Researcher**: Deployed via the server with real-time **Google Search grounding**. It queries live indices for recent factual nodes on the user\'s topic and extracts structured JSON outputs with citations (`source`, `keyPoint`, and `excerpt`).\n- **Agent 2: Syntax Editor**: Takes the structured output of Agent 1 as raw cognitive data, then processes, rewrites, and condenses the material. It yields a synthesized briefing featuring an engaging introduction, 3 to 5 impact-driven bullet points, and a critical one-line takeaway.\n- **Pipeline Separator**: The agents are executed sequentially as separate modular modules via a secure full-stack backend endpoint.\n\n#### 2. Cold Storage Persistence\n- **Firestore Integration**: Every successful briefing is committed to a dedicated Firestore collection, retaining the topic, UTC timestamp, raw Researcher facts, and the finalized Editor synthesis.\n- **History Retrieval**: A chronological indexing engine queries Firestore (`newest first`) on bootstrap and reload, allowing users to re-open any historical digest instantly.\n\n#### 3. Retro-Futurist Interface Design\n- **Glitch Art Visuals**: The workspace is built inside a pitch-black CRT overlay styled with linear scanlines and high-contrast **Neon Cyan vs. Magenta** digital boundaries.\n- **Diagnostics Logger**: A real-time telemetry terminal mimics mainframe processes, logging typewriter style system states (e.g., probe dispatching, schema commit, etc.) as the sequential agents compute.\n- **Multi-Agent Debugger**: An expandable inspector allows the operator to toggle and view Agent 1\'s raw search findings side-by-side with Agent 2\'s finalized synthesis, validating the multi-agent sequence.\n\n---\n\n### // VERIFICATION STATUS\n```\n> tsc --noEmit\nLINTING COMPLETED SUCCESSFULLY [0 WARNINGS / 0 ERRORS]\n\n> npm run build\nCOMPILATION COMPLETED SUCCESSFULLY [dist/server.cjs CREATED]\n```"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 4
      nanos: 634908478
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
